negative.review:
[b] tl;dr [/b] - generally fun game before you hit ~5hrs of playtime, unfun cock and ball torture afterwards.

3D survivorslike gameplay feels genuinely fun and fresh, love the movement (yet despise the amount of displacement effects and knockback), hitting the bhops tingles my autism in a good way, but the cracks in gameplay quickly start to show:
- Nonexistent build variety with the t3 and above builds being either playable (aka 1 or 2 combinations) or unplayable (literally everything else);
- Weird progression (although I don't ~mind~ lack of metaprogression in a game like this, locking weapon and tome slots behind quite a handful of challenges (slightly less egregious compared to the release) is certainly a... choice. The more stuff you unlock, the more punished you are - even though you can disable the unlocks from your roster, it feels weird removing 95% of the stuff you've worked for);
- Godawful final boss I don't think anyone likes;
- [A matter of personal preference, but still] le painfully outdated dank memes xD in big '25.

Is it good? 
It's ~ [b] alright [/b]~ but unfortunately the novelty quickly wears off. Still puzzling to me how it got astroturfed into what is pretty much the second coming of Christ, despite being middle of the pack game of its genre.
